title: AWS DeepLens Powered Cat Flap
description:
Learn more about AWS Machine Learning at - https://amzn.to/2YYTmjW. 
AWS DeepLens helps put machine learning in the hands of developers, literally, with a fully programmable video camera, tutorials, code, and pre-trained models designed to expand deep learning skills. See how Ben Hamm developed cat flap using ML and DeepLens to stop his "cat" Metric from bringing home dead and half-dead prey in the middle of the night and waking him up.

title: How to Build an AWS DeepLens Project Using Amazon SageMaker
description:
This step-by-step tutorial will help guide you through creating a model using Amazon SageMaker and importing it to AWS DeepLens. You will set up a SageMaker instance, import and configure an external notebook from GitHub and import the externally trained model to your AWS DeepLens. Learn more at - https://amzn.to/2JPChxR.

This is video 4 of 4. Watch the entire series here - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLhr1KZpdzukcgnZzblsxDt8YqS78bDhYl.

title: How to Create and Deploy a Deep Learning Project With AWS DeepLens
description:
This step-by-step tutorial will guide you through creating and deploying your first deep learning model with AWS DeepLens. You will create a project, then deploy and view the project output directly from the device. Learn more at - https://amzn.to/2jA7vOB.

This is video 2 of 4. Watch the entire series here - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLhr1KZpdzukcgnZzblsxDt8YqS78bDhYl.

description: Amazon's Worldwide Sustainability Manager, Alexis Fuge, and her team talk about some of the innovative work Amazon has been doing to use DeepLens to help with waste management. Learn more about the AWS DeepLens Challenge at - https://amzn.to/2pvQjMY.

title: How to Extend a Deep Leaning Project with AWS DeepLens
description:
This step-by-step tutorial will help guide you through extending a model with AWS DeepLens. You will capture the events from your AWS DeepLens model and put them in a queue ready for further processing. You can then extend the models utilizing AWS Lambda functions. Learn more at - https://amzn.to/2wb97Yc.

This is video 3 of 4. Watch the entire series here - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLhr1KZpdzukcgnZzblsxDt8YqS78bDhYl.

description: Hopecam's founder, Len Forkas, talks about how you can use AWS DeepLens to boost mental or physical health and support children overcome challenges with cancer. Learn more about the AWS DeepLens Challenge at - https://amzn.to/2PVW2GU.

description: Watch the AWS DeepLens demo by Dr. Matt Wood at re:Invent 2017. Learn more about AWS DeepLens at - http://amzn.to/2AmP7QP.

title: AWS Dev Day Australia 2018 - Intelligence of things: IoT, AWS DeepLens and Amazon SageMaker
description:
Learn more about AWS Greengrass at - https://amzn.to/2wk88BF
With IoT, Machine Learning is going everywhere. Using Amazon SageMaker it's never been easier to build Intelligent Things. In this session we look at how we can push intelligence from cloud-trained models to the edge using AWS Greengrass and explore how devices such as AWS DeepLens make it easy to bring intelligence to your things.

Speaker: Jan Haak, AWS Global Solutions Architect

title: Demonstration: Automating Recycling
description: The "Smart Recycle Arm" recognizes items that are recyclable and pushes them to the correct bin. Using the AWS DeepLens, the worldâ€™s first deep learning enabled video camera for developers, it can differentiate between recyclable and non recyclable items. A robotic arm which pushes the items into the correct bin.

title: AWS DeepLens Challenge #1: Inclusivity
description: The first project in the AWS DeepLens Challenge focuses on inclusivity, here being described by Northwest Center CEO Gene Boes. For more on the AWS DeepLens Challenge, go to https://amzn.to/2L5ytJS.

title: AWS Builders' Day | Machine Learning at the Edge with Amazon Greengrass ML and AWS DeepLens
description:
Check out the upcoming schedule, previous recordings, and links to the resources discussed at - http://amzn.to/2Hg24i7.

Amazon AI services bring natural language understanding (NLU), automatic speech recognition (ASR), visual search and image recognition, text-to-speech (TTS), and machine learning (ML) technologies within the reach of every developer. Learn how you can easily add these powerful features to your applications to enhance the way they interact with the real world.

Get started with Machine Learning at https://aws.amazon.com/machine-learning/.
